<text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
  <body>
    <div rend="parallel">
      <lg xml:id="TPa1">
<l>mārkaḻit tiṅkaḷ mati niṟainta naṉṉāḷāl</l>
<l>nīrāṭap pōtuvīr pōtumiṉō nēriḻaiyīr</l>
<l>cīr malkum āyppāṭic celvac ciṟumīrkāḷ</l>
<l>kūrvēl koṭuntoḻilaṉ nantakōpaṉ kumaraṉ</l>
<l>ērārnta kaṇṇi yacōtai iḷam ciṅkam</l>
<l>kār mēṉi ceṅkaṇ katir matiyam pōl mukattāṉ</l>
<l>nārāyaṇaṉē namakkē paṟai taruvāṉ</l>
<l>pārōr pukaḻap paṭintēlōr empāvāy.</l>
      </lg>
      <lg xml:lang="en">
<l>Āl! O those who have proceeded to bathe in the month of Mārkaḻi,</l>
<l rend="indent">on a good day filled with a full moon!</l>
<l>O ladies adorned with fine jewels! Will you not go [with me]?</l>
<l>O you wealthy girls from the cowherds’ hamlet/Gokula abounding with prosperity!</l>
<l>The Son of Nandagopa with a sharp spear [and] a cruel occupation,</l>
<l>The young Lion of Yaśoda with beautiful eyes,</l>
<l>[with] a cloud[-like] body, red eyes,</l>
<l rend="indent">[and] with a face like the sun [and] the moon, Nārāyaṇa Himself</l>
<l>will give the paṟai-drum solely to us!</l>
<l>Bathe, so that the people of the world praise [us].</l>
<l>O our maidens, accept [and] consider [this] attentively!</l>
      </lg>
    </div>
  </body>
